<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-03T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-03T13:00:00-05:00" n="1232" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1232">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 867.48/293</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-03T13:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 3, 1916, 1 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2678. Your 1821, May 21, and Department’s 2600, May 24.<note n="1" xml:id="d1232fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_851">p.
                                    851</ref>.</note> Have you yet urged Ottoman Government to take
                                steps for protection Christians in Syria? For your information.
                                Report from Cairo states Syria famine-stricken, people dying
                                starvation by thousands, particularly Lebanon. Estimated 80,000 dead
                                starvation Lebanon alone up to beginning May. Also reported distress
                                not due entirely natural war conditions, but to political design on
                                part Turkish Government to exterminate by starvation Christian
                                population. Eyewitnesses report military cordon prevents entry of
                                food into Lebanon. There is strong feeling of sympathy in the United
                                States for destitute in Syria, and many would like to send relief if
                                this can be done. Ascertain whether Turkish Government will permit
                                relief supplies to be sent Lebanon and other parts Syria, to be
                                distributed by neutral committee.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>